  "prompt": "How long does diarrhea last?",
  "response": "The duration of diarrhea can vary depending on its cause. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. **Acute Diarrhea**: Typically lasts from 1 to 2 days and often resolves on its own. This is most commonly caused by infections (viral, bacterial, or parasitic), food poisoning, or certain medications.\n\n2. **Persistent Diarrhea**: Lasts longer than 2 weeks but less than 4 weeks. This may still be related to infections or could indicate an underlying condition.\n\n3. **Chronic Diarrhea**: Persists for 4 weeks or longer. Chronic diarrhea is often linked to ongoing conditions such as irritable bowel syndrome (IBS), inflammatory bowel disease (IBD), celiac disease, or certain chronic infections.\n\n### When to Seek Medical Attention:\n- Diarrhea lasts more than 2 days (for adults) or 24 hours (for children).\n- Severe dehydration symptoms (e.g., dry mouth, dizziness, dark urine, or lethargy).\n- Blood or mucus in the stool.\n- High fever (above 102\u00b0F or 39\u00b0C).\n- Severe abdominal or rectal pain.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure or concerned, it\u2019s always best to consult a healthcare professional for proper evaluation and treatment.",
